<doc id="774305" wikidata="Q14878666" url="?curid=774305" title="Rhomborhina">
<text>Rhomborhina is a genus of large scarab beetles described by Hope in 1837. They are members of the subfamily Cetoniinae. They mostly live in East and South Asia. The name is frequently misspelled as Rhomborrhina following an unjustified change by Hermann Burmeister in 1842.

==Species==
* &quot;Rhomborhina aokii&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina bossioni&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina bousqueti&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina castanea&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina folschveilleri&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina formosana&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina fuscipes&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina gestroi&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina gigantea&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina hamai&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina hiekei&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina kurosawai&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina mellyi&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina microcephala&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina polita&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina resplendens&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina splendida&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina taiwana&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina unicolor&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina violacea&quot; 
* &quot;Rhomborhina yunnana&quot; 

