<doc id="774325" wikidata="Q999236" url="?curid=774325" title="Halsua">
<text>Halsua () is a municipality of Finland.

Halsua is located in the province of Western Finland and is part of the Central Ostrobothnia region. The municipality has a population of about 1200 in 2019&#x27;s and covers an area of of which is water. The population density is .

Neighbouring municipalities are Kaustinen, Kokkola, Lestijärvi, Perho and Veteli.

The municipality is unilingually Finnish.

