<doc id="774372" wikidata="Q1589322" url="?curid=774372" title="Haukivuori">
<text>Haukivuori is a former municipality of Finland located in the province of Eastern Finland and part of the Southern Savonia region. The municipality had a population of 2,361 and covered an area of 505.11 km2, of which 108.07 km2 is water. The population density was 4.7 inhabitants per km2. On 1 January 2007, Haukivuori was incorporated into the city of Mikkeli.

Haukivuori center is c. 41 km by road from Mikkeli center. Kouvola-Iisalmi railway line goes through Haukivuori.

The municipality was unilingually Finnish.

==People born in Haukivuori==
* Sari Essayah (1967–)

